overview: On a sleepy summer night in 2004, eyes peer into the world-wide-web: traveling between conspiracy sites, malware, porn, and mp3 databases in an attempt to lose (find) themselves. Passing through blog graveyards, broken hyperlinks, and digital spirits, they begin to realize the Internet is so much more. Lost websites, anon forums, and inexplicable pixels singing to a prepubescent soul . An ode to the 2000s webpage and flash game culture.
title: “(ಥ﹏ಥ) ✧_My parents are cia PSY0PS_!!!* ಠ_ಠ"
